4
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:46,000
飞天大盗 第2季第6集
S02E06 Eye of the Beholder

5
00:01:11,300 --> 00:01:13,370
- 你不能打权杖钻石的主意 - 为什么不能?
- You can't nick the Crown Jewels. - Why not?

6
00:01:13,460 --> 00:01:15,570
为什么?我会告诉你为什么不能
Why not?I'll tell you why not.

7
00:01:15,660 --> 00:01:17,690
因为那是没有爱国心的开始
Because it's unpatriotic for a start.

8
00:01:17,780 --> 00:01:19,570
另外,我可不能想像...
Besides which,I don't fancy being banged up...

9
00:01:19,660 --> 00:01:21,890
在以后的300年内都被吊在伦敦塔上
in the Tower of London for the next 300 years.

10
00:01:21,980 --> 00:01:26,010
- 这一次,我觉得Danny或许讲到重点了 - 耶,谢谢,Stacie
- For once,I think Danny may have a point. - Yeah,thank you,Stacie.

11
00:01:26,260 --> 00:01:27,480
你的"这一次"是什么意思?
What do you mean "for once"?

12
00:01:27,580 --> 00:01:29,930
如果我们被抓住了 他们会把钥匙扔掉的,是不是?
If we get caught,they'll throw away the key,won't they?

13
00:01:30,020 --> 00:01:34,210
完全正确.我真是迫不及待要去监狱了 睡都睡不着
Exactly.I'm too pretty to go to prison.I'll never get any sleep.

14
00:01:35,380 --> 00:01:38,250
算我老派吧.但我会让大家避免被抓住的
Call me old-fashioned,but I was hoping to avoid getting caught.

15
00:01:38,340 --> 00:01:40,530
我们在说的可是一场世纪的犯罪
We're talking about the crime of the century.

16
00:01:40,620 --> 00:01:42,920
有一队私人收藏家愿意付出...
There's a band of private collectors who are willing to pay...

17
00:01:43,020 --> 00:01:46,850
小小的金钱把非洲之星第一 加入到他们的收藏中
a small fortune to add the First Star of Africa to their collection.

18
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:49,090
- 我们能找到他们吗? - 已经在进行中了
- Can we find them? - All in hand.

19
00:01:49,660 --> 00:01:51,650
非洲之星第一
The First Star of Africa.

20
00:01:52,020 --> 00:01:56,050
530.2克拉.也被称为库利南1号...
530.2 carats.Also known as the Cullinan I...

21
00:01:56,180 --> 00:01:59,370
1905年在南非发现的库利南钻石 被切割成9块后...
because it's the largest of the nine stones cut from the Cullinan diamond...

22
00:01:59,460 --> 00:02:01,890
这是最大的一块,因此得名
discovered in South Africa in 1905.

23
00:02:02,580 --> 00:02:05,770
现在被镶在英国国王的权杖上
It's now set in the head of the Royal Scepter.

24
00:02:05,940 --> 00:02:07,930
无价之宝
It is priceless.

25
00:02:08,380 --> 00:02:10,760
老家在伦敦塔里
Home is the Tower of London.

26
00:02:11,780 --> 00:02:15,250
历史上只有一次对权杖钻石进行过偷窃
There has only ever been one attempt to steal the Crown Jewels.

27
00:02:15,460 --> 00:02:18,210
是Colonel Blood在1671年偷的
And that was by Colonel Blood in 1671.

28
00:02:18,420 --> 00:02:20,170
- 他怎么样了? - 失败
- What happened to him? - He failed.

29
00:02:20,260 --> 00:02:23,850
很好,那我们要做什么?游过护城河还是去攀登碉堡?
Great,so what are we gonna do?Swim the moat or scale the battlements?

30
00:02:23,940 --> 00:02:26,810
不需要.国王的权杖要被搬动了...
No need.The Royal Scepter's being moved...

31
00:02:27,060 --> 00:02:29,090
给了我们一生唯一一次的机会
giving us a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.

32
00:02:29,180 --> 00:02:30,490
它为什么会被搬动呢?
Why is it being moved?

33
00:02:30,580 --> 00:02:32,650
现在皇家珠宝商正在对它进行清洗...
Right now it's being cleaned by the Royal Jewelers...

34
00:02:32,740 --> 00:02:34,970
- 然后又会被搬动 - 去哪里?
- and after that it'll be moved again. - Where?

35
00:02:36,580 --> 00:02:39,970
市政厅艺廊正在举办一次非洲展览...
The Guildhall Art Gallery is holding a major African exhibition...

36
00:02:40,060 --> 00:02:42,010
来配合英联邦首脑会议
to coincide with the Commonwealth summit.

37
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:44,530
从后天开始...
It starts the day after tomorrow...

38
00:02:45,460 --> 00:02:48,330
而这颗非洲之星就是中心装饰品
and the Star of Africa is to be the centerpiece.

39
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:52,050
好了.想想吧
All right.Think of it.

40
00:02:52,460 --> 00:02:55,370
本世纪最伟大的一次记录,或是最后一次
The biggest score of this century or the last.

41
00:02:55,460 --> 00:02:59,370
某些会在100年,甚至200年 以后还被记住的事情
Something that will be remembered 100,even 200 years from now.

42
00:03:01,340 --> 00:03:05,170
一切我懂的,一切我所学到的 都在等着这一时刻
Everything I know,everything I've learned has been waiting for this moment.

43
00:03:07,580 --> 00:03:09,770
没有比这更大的东西会再出现在我们面前
Nothing this big will ever come our way again.

44
00:03:10,340 --> 00:03:13,290
而不利的是,如果我们被抓住了...
The downside is,if we get caught...

45
00:03:13,820 --> 00:03:17,410
我们都会在监狱里面待上很长时间
we all go to prison for a very long time.

46
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:43,370
- 你还好吗,Mick? - 是啊,就那样吧
- You all right,Mick?You on your own? - Yeah,looks that way.

47
00:03:46,780 --> 00:03:47,810
干杯
Cheers.

48
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:03,290
如果我不够了解你,我会说你在生气
If I didn't know better,I'd say you were sulking.

49
00:04:03,620 --> 00:04:05,050
真的吗?
Really?

50
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:06,890
你在期盼什么?
What did you expect?

51
00:04:06,980 --> 00:04:09,770
你要求他们把余生都压在这一次上
You asked them to put the rest of their lives on the line.

52
00:04:10,340 --> 00:04:11,480
的确是
Yes,I did.

53
00:04:11,620 --> 00:04:14,850
你掷骰子,他们紧紧盯着.就这样
You rolled the dice,they came up snake eyes.It happens.

54
00:04:16,620 --> 00:04:17,890
是啊
Yep.

55
00:04:21,580 --> 00:04:23,050
就告诉我一件事情
Just tell me one thing.

56
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:25,960
为什么?
Why?

57
00:04:27,060 --> 00:04:31,850
因为300年来没有一个人敢对此进行尝试
Because no one has ever dared attempt anything this big for 300 years.

58
00:04:31,940 --> 00:04:34,090
- 就这样? - 对于我来说,是的
- And that's it? - For me,yes.

59
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:39,730
瞧,这是镇里最大的游戏
Look,this is the biggest game in town.

60
00:04:40,420 --> 00:04:42,690
如果我们不干,我们还能干什么
If we're not here,we're not anywhere.

61
00:04:43,660 --> 00:04:45,130
我可以了解
I can see that.

62
00:04:45,980 --> 00:04:47,290
你瞧,Mickey...
You see,Mickey...

63
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:49,970
之前我有我自己的顾虑...
I had my doubts earlier...

64
00:04:51,140 --> 00:04:52,450
但你可以把我算在里面
but you can count me in.

65
00:04:54,260 --> 00:04:56,330
谢谢,Danny.一语值千金
Thanks,Danny.That's worth a lot.

66
00:04:56,780 --> 00:04:59,340
但如果没有Stacie和Ash的话还是不行
But this can't happen without Stacie and Ash.

67
00:04:59,420 --> 00:05:00,810
真高兴听到你这么说
Glad to hear it.

68
00:05:01,220 --> 00:05:03,780
- 他生气了吗,Albert? - 我想是的,是啊
- Was he sulking,Albert? - I'm afraid so,yeah.

69
00:05:03,980 --> 00:05:06,090
- 哦哦 - 我没有生气
- Diddums. - I was not sulking.

70
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:08,640
嗯,装的不错,看起来你自己承认了啊
Well,it worked,looks like you're getting your own way.

71
00:05:08,740 --> 00:05:10,850
不,等等,拜托
No,now,wait a minute,come on.

72
00:05:10,940 --> 00:05:12,930
这件事情对这里的任何人来说都 是件大事...
This thing is far too big for anyone to be here...

73
00:05:13,020 --> 00:05:14,650
比他们想做的任何事情都要大
for any other reason than they want to be.

74
00:05:14,740 --> 00:05:15,960
你现在可不能反悔了
You can't bottle it now.

75
00:05:16,060 --> 00:05:18,570
啊哦,一开始他生气,而现在他却 想收手不干
Cor blimey,first he sulks,now he's trying to back out.

76
00:05:18,660 --> 00:05:21,040
我没有要收手,但是...
I'm not backing out,but...

77
00:05:22,020 --> 00:05:25,530
如果我们要做的话,我们需要万分小心
if we do this,we do it with our eyes open.

78
00:05:26,580 --> 00:05:29,410
嘿,如果我们不能...
Hey,if we can't do it...

79
00:05:30,020 --> 00:05:31,370
还有谁能?
who can?

80
00:05:32,020 --> 00:05:34,650
- Eddie - 记在账单上
- Eddie. - On the tab.

81
00:05:35,420 --> 00:05:37,770
那么,对你们这群家伙来说或 这次是要转变方向了?
So,is this a change of direction for you boys?

82
00:05:37,860 --> 00:05:40,650
- 你们现在成小偷了? - 只是想赚点生活费,Benny
- You're thieves now? - Just trying to earn a living,Benny.

83
00:05:40,740 --> 00:05:43,690
跟我说说吧.这里不会再有正直的骗子了
Tell me about it,there are no honest crooks anymore.

84
00:05:44,180 --> 00:05:45,810
每个人都企图占你便宜
Everyone tries to screw you.

85
00:05:45,900 --> 00:05:49,130
我,我被占便宜的次数比妓女接的客还多
Me,I've been screwed more times than a coachload of hookers.

86
00:05:49,940 --> 00:05:52,210
我看你说话还是很间接明了的啊,Benjamin
I see you still have a wonderful way with words,Benjamin.

87
00:05:52,300 --> 00:05:54,890
不要跟我说简洁明了,Stroller先生
Don't talk to me about words,Mr.Stroller.

88
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:57,370
握握手就可以了
Time was a handshake was enough.

89
00:05:57,460 --> 00:06:00,810
现在,大家都像14岁的小毛头 带着没剔干净的鼻毛...
Now,everyone's 14,with spots and rings in their noses...

90
00:06:01,100 --> 00:06:03,610
用天花乱坠的说辞来欺骗你
all using fancy words to screw you.

91
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:06,330
"这个的5%,那个的两成"
"Five percent of this.Two pints of that."

92
00:06:06,620 --> 00:06:09,970
"钱的10%下个星期三就付给你"
"Ten pence in the pound and pay you next Wednesday."

93
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:13,170
- 是啊,这个世界已经大不同了 - 就是这样
- Yeah,it's a different world. - That it is.

94
00:06:13,740 --> 00:06:17,770
我?我拥有的已经足够了 明年,我就会把所有的都变卖
Me?I've had enough.Next year,I sell up.

95
00:06:18,220 --> 00:06:19,930
让其他人去被占便宜吧
Let someone else get screwed.

96
00:06:25,260 --> 00:06:29,290
那么.伟大的Mickey Bricks 和Albert Stroller
So.The great Mickey Bricks and Albert Stroller.

97
00:06:30,420 --> 00:06:34,450
叫我中国佬吧,但我猜 你们没有一大包的汽车无线电
Call me a Chinaman but my guess is you don't have a bag full of car radios.

98
00:06:35,180 --> 00:06:37,290
- 不是的 - 那到底是什么?
- Not quite. - So what is it?

99
00:06:39,180 --> 00:06:40,730
权杖钻石?
The Crown Jewels?

100
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:48,410
告诉我你们不是真的要
Please tell me you're not serious.

101
00:06:48,540 --> 00:06:53,480
我们要找的是一些私人收藏家 的秘密标价
What we're looking for are a few select private collectors to put in sealed bids.

102
00:06:53,780 --> 00:06:56,610
- 一场拍卖? - 赢家获得所有的
- An auction? - Winner takes all.

103
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:02,890
我有多少时间准备?
How long have I got?

104
00:07:03,020 --> 00:07:05,930
我们找到了为那家展览馆 做清理的公司
We've found the cleaning company who has the contract for the gallery.

105
00:07:06,140 --> 00:07:08,440
他们雇佣东欧的工人
They employ mostly Eastern European workers.

106
00:07:08,540 --> 00:07:11,000
- 你是说会便宜些 - 差不多
- You mean cheap. - Precisely.

107
00:07:11,260 --> 00:07:14,290
你今晚就开始.那些是详细资料
And you start tonight.Those are the details.

108
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:16,280
好的
All right.

109
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:17,720
- 哈? - 是我
- Hello? - It's me.

110
00:07:17,820 --> 00:07:20,650
- Benny,你有什么可以告诉我的? - 不简单啊
- Benny,what have you got for me? - It wasn't easy.

111
00:07:20,860 --> 00:07:23,810
我不得不亲自告诉你 我觉得你们太愚蠢了
I have to say that personally,I think you're insane.

112
00:07:24,180 --> 00:07:27,210
但如果你们成功了 我就能帮你们找到5个出价者
But if you pull it off,I've got five bidders lined up.

113
00:07:27,380 --> 00:07:29,050
都是最一流的
All topnotch.

114
00:07:29,140 --> 00:07:30,570
我就知道你是干这个的不二人选
I knew you were the man for the job.

115
00:07:30,660 --> 00:07:33,090
密封的标价单会送到你的旅馆去
Sealed bids will be delivered to your hotel.

116
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:35,170
好的,Benny,我会去接收的
Okay,Benny,I'll be in touch.

117
00:07:36,740 --> 00:07:38,490
- 怎么样? - 我们开始吧
- Well? - We are on.

118
00:07:38,620 --> 00:07:41,130
谢谢.实在是太好了.不
Thank you.That's blinding.No.

119
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:45,810
- 不.相信我,非常感谢 - Danny,你在干吗?
- No.Believe me,thank you very much. - Danny,what are you doing?

120
00:07:45,900 --> 00:07:48,850
- 电话奖励,一分钟一英镑 - 什么?
- Premium phone line,50 quid a minute. - What?

121
00:07:48,940 --> 00:07:52,450
我设置了这些线路中的一条 每次有人拨打这个号码...
I set up one of these lines.Every time somebody phones this number...

122
00:07:52,540 --> 00:07:54,570
我的口袋里就会进账1英镑
I get 50 quid in me pocket.

123
00:07:54,660 --> 00:07:56,690
但你怎么让别人打你这个号码呢?
But how are you going to get people to phone the number?

124
00:07:56,780 --> 00:07:59,810
不,瞧,这就是我天才的地方
No,listen,this is where the genius comes in.

125
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:01,450
因为我无需这样,你瞧
'Cause I don't have to,you see.

126
00:08:01,540 --> 00:08:05,290
我所要做的,就是我借个电话打 这个号码
All I got to do,yeah,is I borrow a phone and I call the number.

127
00:08:05,380 --> 00:08:08,290
是的,然后它们会认为我花了10 先令的话费...
Yeah,then they think I'm making a 10p call...

128
00:08:08,380 --> 00:08:10,450
但我口袋里却已经进账了1英镑
but I'm getting 50 big ones in me pocket.

129
00:08:10,540 --> 00:08:11,650
- Danny - 是的,Mickey
- Danny. - Yeah,Mickey.

130
00:08:11,740 --> 00:08:13,330
你不让我用信用卡的
You did stop me using the credit cards.

131
00:08:13,420 --> 00:08:15,690
- 他们会留下罪证的 - 但它们管用
- They were very bad copies. - But they did work.

132
00:08:15,780 --> 00:08:17,810
我们已经被一家餐馆扔出来了
We got thrown out of a restaurant.

133
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:21,370
好吧,你对的.但我还是有些吃住的问题
Granted,everyone,but I had a few teething troubles.

134
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:24,290
Danny,我劝你最好专心到我们 手上的工作中
Danny,I would much rather you focused on the job in hand.

135
00:08:24,380 --> 00:08:28,080
我一直关心的,伙计们,我关心的 这只是我的一点点副业而已
I'm focused,gang,I'm focused.This is just a little sideline.

136
00:08:28,180 --> 00:08:32,250
我要弄点点钱在你让我们被捕后 还能买一些烟草
Make a little bit of money to buy some tobacco when you get us all arrested.

137
00:08:32,700 --> 00:08:36,290
Eddie,我能借用下你的电话吗,伙计?给我老妈打个电话
Eddie,can I borrow your phone,mate?Just got to phone me old mom.

138
00:08:40,980 --> 00:08:41,960
哈,妈妈?
Hello,Mom?

139
00:08:55,820 --> 00:08:57,330
我会看着你
I'll be watching you.

140
00:09:13,620 --> 00:09:17,530
- 我刚泡了一壶茶 - 哦,谢谢
- I've just made a pot of tea. - Yes,thank you.

141
00:09:18,140 --> 00:09:19,970
我马上就干完了
I will just finish my work.

142
00:09:20,220 --> 00:09:22,890
你会把清漆都磨掉的 你还在磨
You'll wear the varnish off,you polish it any more.

143
00:09:22,980 --> 00:09:24,650
但我想干得更好一些
But I want to do a good job.

144
00:09:24,740 --> 00:09:28,050
是的.但如果你喝杯茶后会干得更好
Yes,and you'll do a better job with a cup of tea inside you.

145
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:30,970
我5分钟就好
I be five minute.

146
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:32,680
Lily
Lily.

147
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:38,170
- 那里怎么了? - 有某个特别的展览
- What is happening in there? - Some kind of special exhibition.

148
00:09:38,380 --> 00:09:39,970
非常机密的
All very hush- hush.

149
00:10:34,340 --> 00:10:36,930
- 练习练习脚步 - 那音乐呢?
- Practicing a few moves. - And the music?

150
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:38,690
给我一些情绪
Get me in the mood.

151
00:10:40,180 --> 00:10:42,450
- 对汤姆克鲁斯很管用,不是吗? - 好吧
- It worked for Tom Cruise,didn't it? - Okay.

152
00:10:42,540 --> 00:10:44,730
