170
00:11:24,340 --> 00:11:27,690
不.再给我一点时间,我会找出方法的
No.Just give me a bit more time.I'll see what I can do.

171
00:11:28,460 --> 00:11:30,090
同时...
In the meantime...

172
00:11:31,020 --> 00:11:32,240
我上班要迟到了
I'm late for work.

173
00:11:37,580 --> 00:11:40,170
是的
Yeah.

174
00:11:41,580 --> 00:11:43,210
我再打给你吧
I'm gonna have to call you back.

175
00:12:23,300 --> 00:12:24,330
你好啊,Benny
Hello,Benny.

176
00:12:35,060 --> 00:12:38,210
这是在你的仓库里面找到的东西清单
This is an inventory of what was found in your warehouse.

177
00:12:38,740 --> 00:12:40,770
而这是失窃报告的物品清单...
And this is a list of items reported stolen...

178
00:12:40,860 --> 00:12:43,570
就是在过去7天左右伦敦市郊失窃的物品
in the Greater London area over the past seven days.

179
00:12:44,020 --> 00:12:45,955
你可以看出来它们是一致的
As you can see they're virtually identical.

180
00:12:45,956 --> 00:12:47,890
我都是通过正规渠道买进来的
I bought every item there in good faith.

181
00:12:47,980 --> 00:12:51,010
这样的话,你就应该有收据,发票
In which case you'll have receipts,invoices.

182
00:12:51,420 --> 00:12:53,010
提供者的姓名和地址
Names and addresses of suppliers.

183
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:55,090
- 我们遇到火灾了 - 哦,是的
- We had a fire. - Oh,yes.

184
00:12:56,460 --> 00:12:57,650
的确是
Of course you did.

185
00:12:58,300 --> 00:13:00,250
犯罪记录
Crime report.

186
00:13:01,020 --> 00:13:02,970
有一整箱的电脑装备...
A container- Ioad of computer equipment...

187
00:13:03,060 --> 00:13:05,620
在三个星期之前被人从码头偷走了
was stolen from the docks three weeks ago.

188
00:13:05,980 --> 00:13:08,050
昨天早上被我们找到
They found the container yesterday morning.

189
00:13:08,700 --> 00:13:10,290
有人试图烧毁它
Someone had tried to burn it.

190
00:13:10,540 --> 00:13:13,890
这年头的小孩,无组织无纪律
Kids these days.No discipline.

191
00:13:16,020 --> 00:13:17,410
火被扑灭了
The fire went out.

192
00:13:18,180 --> 00:13:20,370
我们采集了指纹...
We dusted for prints...

193
00:13:21,060 --> 00:13:22,930
你永远也猜不到我们找到了什么
and you'll never guess what we found.

194
00:13:25,020 --> 00:13:26,210
完全匹配
Perfect match.

195
00:13:27,180 --> 00:13:29,610
一目了然,Benny
Bang to rights,Benny.

196
00:13:31,980 --> 00:13:35,890
- 会判多久,Wells先生? - 根据你的记录,15年
- How long,Mr.Wells? - With your form,fifteen years.

197
00:13:36,820 --> 00:13:39,730
如果你认罪,或许是判12年
You take a guilty,you might get 12.

198
00:13:41,900 --> 00:13:43,090
那么?
Well?

199
00:13:49,140 --> 00:13:50,490
等等
Wait.

200
00:13:54,020 --> 00:13:57,560
- 做个交易如何? - 什么样的交易?
- What about a deal? - What kind of deal?

201
00:13:57,740 --> 00:14:00,300
最近会有一起权杖钻石的抢劫
The imminent robbery of the Crown Jewels.

202
00:14:05,580 --> 00:14:08,210
- 你看看有多么宏伟... - 你说了7次了
- You saw how magnificent... - You said it seven times.

203
00:14:08,300 --> 00:14:10,170
- 不 - Morgan先生
- No. - Mr.Morgan.

204
00:14:10,940 --> 00:14:13,170
对不起打搅你,管理人员想知道...
I'm sorry to bother you,only the manager wondered...

205
00:14:13,260 --> 00:14:15,610
你们是否可以付一下最近的账单?
whether you could bring your account up- to-date?

206
00:14:16,620 --> 00:14:18,130
- 已经是一大笔钱了 - 哦,是啊
- It is rather a lot. - Yeah,it is.

207
00:14:18,220 --> 00:14:19,200
- 我没有 - 你有
- I didn't have that. - You did.

208
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:20,970
- 你有吗? - 我没有,我不喜欢...
- Did you have that? - I didn't,I don't like... 

209
00:14:21,060 --> 00:14:23,290
- 那谁有? - 够了,这不是问题
- Who had that? - Enough.It's not a problem.

210
00:14:23,540 --> 00:14:24,890
嘿
Hey.

211
00:14:25,460 --> 00:14:28,370
把你的手收住吧,伙计 就放在那里,我来搞定
Put your hand in there,mate.Keep it in there,I'll get this.

212
00:14:28,460 --> 00:14:31,130
- 谢谢 - 没事,不客气
- Thank you. - All right,you're very welcome.

213
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:34,410
瞧,亲爱的.你在刷卡的时候...
Listen,love,while you put that through the old switcherooney...

214
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:35,930
- 我能用你的电话吗? - 当然
- can I use your phone? - Of course.

215
00:14:36,020 --> 00:14:37,410
给我老妈打个电话
Got to phone me old mom.

216
00:14:45,220 --> 00:14:46,330
你好,妈妈?
Hello,Mom?

217
00:15:34,660 --> 00:15:36,290
你不应该在这里的
You shouldn't be in here.

218
00:15:38,300 --> 00:15:40,290
但我必须处理一下地板
But I have to do floors.

219
00:15:40,380 --> 00:15:43,530
不是在这里,亲爱的 他们会带其他人过来的
Not in here,sweetheart.They're bringing other people in.

220
00:15:45,220 --> 00:15:46,690
对不起
I am sorry.

221
00:15:51,580 --> 00:15:54,650
看来我必须看着你了.来吧
I can see I'll have to keep an eye on you.Come on.

222
00:15:55,780 --> 00:15:58,730
来喝杯茶吧.你可以来试试我的波旁茶
Come and have a cuppa.You can try my Bourbons.

223
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:07,090
- Mick - 嘿
- Mick. - Hey.

224
00:16:07,580 --> 00:16:10,140
- 怎么样了? - 我满脚的水泡
- How's it going? - I've got blisters on me blisters.

225
00:16:10,220 --> 00:16:12,810
- 有所得必有所失 - 是啊,是的.谢谢
- No gain without pain. - Yeah,right.Thank you.

226
00:16:12,980 --> 00:16:15,690
瞧,我想我有办法了 门上有个保险装置
Look,I think I've got it.There's a safety feature on the door.

227
00:16:15,780 --> 00:16:19,050
里面时间锁上有个面板 如果有人被锁在里面就能起作用
The time lock's got a panel on the inside,in case anyone gets locked in.

228
00:16:19,140 --> 00:16:20,170
我们能利用这个吗?
So can we use that?

229
00:16:20,260 --> 00:16:22,770
如果我们中有人能在他们关门 之前就在里面
If we can get someone inside before they close it.

230
00:16:22,860 --> 00:16:24,530
嘿,你们是不是该回家了?
Hey,haven't you lot got any homes to go to?

231
00:16:24,620 --> 00:16:27,130
- 再有一会儿就好了,Eddie - 是啊,拜托
- Just a few more minutes,Eddie. - Yeah,come on.

232
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:29,680
- 我可要去睡个好觉了 - 是啊,我也马上就睡了
- I need my beauty sleep. - Yeah,I'll second that.

233
00:16:30,460 --> 00:16:32,250
- 你要喝杯吧? - 你搞得定吗?
- Do you want a drink? - Won't you be lucky?

234
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:36,650
Eddie,我只是想说...
Eddie,I just want to say...

235
00:16:36,740 --> 00:16:39,890
我真的很感激你在我和Ash 一直在工作的时候还在坚持
that I really appreciate you hanging on while Ash and I work something through.

236
00:16:39,980 --> 00:16:43,730
- 是啊,我知道,Mick,但真的很晚了... - 瞧,我来告诉你,好吗
- Yeah,I know,Mick,but it's really late... - Look,I'll tell you what,okay.

237
00:16:43,820 --> 00:16:45,210
我们只要再喝一杯...
We'll just have one more drink...

238
00:16:45,300 --> 00:16:47,970
我保证,我们真的很快就能搞定了
and I promise,we'll be out of your hair really soon.

239
00:16:48,060 --> 00:16:49,370
你看呢?
What do you say?

240
00:16:50,220 --> 00:16:52,650
拜托,我们1点就走
Come on,we'll be gone by 1:00.

241
00:16:52,940 --> 00:16:54,570
但现在已经...
No,but it's gone on....

242
00:16:56,100 --> 00:16:58,170
我发誓现在的时间应该比这个要晚
I could have sworn it was later than that.

243
00:17:01,580 --> 00:17:04,090
- 好吧,你们再喝一杯 - 你太棒了
- Go on,then,one more. - You're a star.

244
00:17:06,980 --> 00:17:09,250
好了,继续.跟我说说这个安全装置
Right,come on,tell me about this safety feature.

245
00:17:14,180 --> 00:17:15,160
长官?
Sir?

246
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:17,370
- DS Hodges? - 是的,长官
- DS Hodges? - Yes,sir.

247
00:17:18,020 --> 00:17:20,531
你的档案告诉我你曾经调查过去年的一个案子
Your DI tells me you were working on a case last year.

248
00:17:20,532 --> 00:17:22,130
Michael Stone?
Michael Stone?

249
00:17:27,860 --> 00:17:30,320
瞧,我们一直在监视Stone
Look,we had Stone under surveillance.

250
00:17:30,660 --> 00:17:31,850
但他不知为何发现了
But he found out somehow.

251
00:17:31,940 --> 00:17:35,090
然后弄了另外一个骗子装扮成了警察
And drafted in another grifter to impersonate a police officer.

252
00:17:35,180 --> 00:17:36,930
案子就搞砸了?
And the case collapsed?

253
00:17:37,660 --> 00:17:40,250
Stone的人介入了调查,长官
Stone's man ran the investigation,sir.

254
00:17:40,900 --> 00:17:42,970
对你来说一定非常难堪
Must have been very embarrassing for you.

255
00:17:43,420 --> 00:17:45,690
对这个部门来说都很难堪,长官
It was embarrassing for the whole department,sir.

256
00:17:45,780 --> 00:17:48,810
- DCI Mullens因为这件事情而丢了工作 - 是吗,现在?
- DCI Mullens lost his job because of it. - Did he,now?

257
00:17:53,140 --> 00:17:54,690
那么....
So....

258
00:17:59,380 --> 00:18:01,250
跟我说说Stone
Tell me about Stone.

259
00:18:01,340 --> 00:18:04,690
- 骗子艺术家... - 不.我知道他做了些什么
- Long con artist... - No.I know what he does.

260
00:18:05,660 --> 00:18:06,880
跟我说说这个人
Tell me about the man.

261
00:18:08,980 --> 00:18:10,890
Mickey Stone是很独特的
Mickey Stone is unique.

262
00:18:11,020 --> 00:18:14,050
他想的和我们不一样 你无法对他进行揣测
He doesn't think like we do.You can't second-guess him.

263
00:18:14,580 --> 00:18:17,490
他给人的印象像是很随意地 走一步算一步
He gives the impression that he's making it all up as he goes along.

264
00:18:17,580 --> 00:18:18,610
不
No.

265
00:18:19,260 --> 00:18:21,970
但每件事情都计划过,非常精确
But everything is planned,precise.

266
00:18:22,060 --> 00:18:24,330
- 为什么是我? - 你抽到了最短的麦杆
- Why me? - You drew the short straw.

267
00:18:25,340 --> 00:18:27,010
我要申述
I demand a recount.

268
00:18:31,460 --> 00:18:33,210
你要推我下去的时候...
So when you gonna push me... 

269
00:18:33,300 --> 00:18:34,890
他会把一堆乱七八糟的事情放在一起...
He puts together complicated...

270
00:18:34,980 --> 00:18:37,970
一堆看起来毫无关系的事情 根本想不到有关
and seemingly unrelated events,impossible to unravel.

271
00:18:38,060 --> 00:18:39,170
服务员,我要一个这个
Waiter,I'll have one of those.

272
00:18:39,260 --> 00:18:41,530
但所有的都指向一个大骗局
But all leading to the big con.

273
00:18:41,660 --> 00:18:44,220
目标越大,他越喜欢
The higher the stakes,the more he likes it.

274
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:45,360
是的,要很长一段时间
Yes,it has been long.

275
00:18:45,460 --> 00:18:47,010
你以为你抓住他的时候...
Just when you think you've got him...

276
00:18:47,100 --> 00:18:48,730
我帮你找了份工作
I've got a job for you.

277
00:18:49,580 --> 00:18:51,330
你坐着吗?
Are you sitting down?

278
00:18:52,780 --> 00:18:56,290
- ...其实你没有 - 听起来,你像是个大粉丝
- ...you haven't. - You sound like a bit of a fan.

279
00:18:56,700 --> 00:19:00,130
绝对不是,长官,他让我看起来 像是个无能的白痴
Hardly,sir,he made me look like an incompetent idiot.

280
00:19:02,820 --> 00:19:04,970
如果能让你找回自我的话如何?
Then how would you like to get your own back?

281
00:19:09,300 --> 00:19:12,250
哦,上帝!对不起
Oh,God!Sorry.

282
00:19:12,420 --> 00:19:14,530
我跟你说,我绝对有些感冒了
I tell you now,I've definitely caught something.

283
00:19:14,620 --> 00:19:17,289
这件事情除非我们能先在展览馆里面安插好人手
Okay,this thing isn't going to work 

284
00:19:17,290 --> 00:19:18,450
否则就无法进行...
unless we can get someone inside the gallery...

285
00:19:18,540 --> 00:19:20,810
特别是在门被锁上以后要在展室里面有人
and in the exhibition room when the doors are locked.

286
00:19:20,900 --> 00:19:24,210
一旦夜间门被关闭,只能从里面打开
Once they're locked for the night,the doors can only be opened from the inside.

287
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:26,010
- 而这就是你要进去的地方 - 怎么进?
- Which is where you come in. - How?

288
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:27,130
Ash
Ash.

289
00:19:27,540 --> 00:19:30,490
我们可以从空中着手以避开压力垫
We can get round the pressure pads by going over the top.

290
00:19:30,580 --> 00:19:33,140
关键问题是,门的时间锁旁边围绕着...
The main problem,though,aside from the time lock on the door...

291
00:19:33,220 --> 00:19:35,730
激光探测器和动作探测器
will be the lasers and the motion detectors.

292
00:19:36,260 --> 00:19:38,930
就像我说的,我们没有办法可以设置旁路...
Like I said,there's no way we can bypass them...

293
00:19:39,020 --> 00:19:41,730
一旦我们步入房间它们就会引发警报
and they'll set the alarms off as soon as we set foot in the room.

294
00:19:41,820 --> 00:19:45,010
- 解决办法呢? - 至今看来唯一可以解决的办法就是...
- Solution? - The only way round it as far as I can see...

295
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:47,770
- 切断电源 - 会让警报关闭吗?
- is to cut the power. - Won't that set the alarms off?

296
00:19:47,860 --> 00:19:50,420
是的,但如果我们在马路外面做...
Yeah,but if we do it outside somewhere in the road...

297
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:51,640
我们会破坏整个街道的电力
we'll knock out the whole street.

298
00:19:51,740 --> 00:19:54,090
- 那所有的警报就都会消失 - 聪明
- There'll be alarms going off everywhere. - Smart.

299
00:19:54,380 --> 00:19:57,970
同时,我们就有30秒的时间来 通过动作探测器...
During that time,we'll have 30 seconds to cover up the motion detectors...

300
00:19:58,060 --> 00:20:01,090
到达门的面板处,关闭激光探测器
and get to the door panel to stop the lasers from coming back on.

301
00:20:02,740 --> 00:20:05,040
- 时间够吗? - 只能那么多时间
- Will that be enough time? - It'll have to be.

302
00:20:05,140 --> 00:20:08,050
一旦有电力恢复,激光和所有 警报设备就会重新开启
Once the genny kicks in,the lasers and everything else will be back on.

303
00:20:08,140 --> 00:20:09,200
闭路电视呢?
CCTV?

304
00:20:09,300 --> 00:20:11,290
我可以在停电的时候重新 设置录像源
I can re-route those at source during the blackout.

305
00:20:11,380 --> 00:20:14,370
- 很好 - 那么,我要做什么?
- Good. - So,what do I have to do then?

306
00:20:14,820 --> 00:20:18,410
在我们打开那扇门之前,必须关闭...
The motion detectors and the lasers have to be disabled from the inside...

307
00:20:18,860 --> 00:20:20,210
动作探测器和激光探测器
before we open the door.

308
00:20:22,100 --> 00:20:25,570
展览有5个主要的负责人
The exhibition has five main exhibitors.

309
00:20:26,260 --> 00:20:29,960
